# Multi-Agent System

This project uses specialized agent personas in `.cursor/agents/`. Each agent has deep knowledge of its domain, follows specific rules, and coordinates with other agents via a clear protocol.

## Agent Roster

| Agent | File | Role | Domain |
|-------|------|------|--------|
| Orchestrator | `.cursor/agents/orchestrator.md` | Decomposes tasks, delegates, merges results | All |
| Planner | `.cursor/agents/planner-agent.md` | Architecture, research, implementation plans | All |
| Frontend | `.cursor/agents/frontend-agent.md` | React, MUI, Redux, i18n code | `expense-tracking-frontend/` |
| Backend | `.cursor/agents/backend-agent.md` | Spring Boot, JPA, Kafka, API code | `expense-tracking-backend/` |
| Database | `.cursor/agents/database-agent.md` | Schema design, JPA entities, migrations, query optimization | `expense-tracking-backend/**/model/`, `**/entity/` |
| QA | `.cursor/agents/qa-agent.md` | Test generation and coverage | `**/*.test.*`, `**/test/**` |
| Security | `.cursor/agents/security-agent.md` | Vulnerability audit, auth review | All (read-only) |
| Reviewer | `.cursor/agents/reviewer-agent.md` | Code review, quality gates | All (read-only) |
| Refactor | `.cursor/agents/refactor-agent.md` | Code cleanup, DRY extraction, tech debt | All (structural changes) |
| Debug | `.cursor/agents/debug-agent.md` | Root cause analysis, systematic troubleshooting | All (diagnostic) |
| DevOps | `.cursor/agents/devops-agent.md` | Docker, CI/CD, environment config, deployment | `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose*`, `Jenkinsfile`, `.env*` |
| Documentation | `.cursor/agents/documentation-agent.md` | API docs, README, OpenAPI, changelog | `*.md`, `**/swagger/**`, `.env.example` |
| i18n & A11y | `.cursor/agents/i18n-accessibility-agent.md` | Translations, WCAG compliance, keyboard nav | `**/i18n/**`, `**/translations/**`, `*.jsx` (a11y audit) |

## How to Use Agents

### Single-Agent Mode (default)

For focused tasks in one domain, read the relevant agent file and adopt its persona:

- Working on frontend? Read `.cursor/agents/frontend-agent.md` and follow its rules
- Working on backend? Read `.cursor/agents/backend-agent.md` and follow its rules
- Writing tests? Read `.cursor/agents/qa-agent.md` and follow its rules
- Security review? Read `.cursor/agents/security-agent.md` and follow its workflow

### Multi-Agent Mode (complex tasks)

For tasks spanning multiple domains, read `.cursor/agents/orchestrator.md` first, then:

1. **Plan**: Read `planner-agent.md`, produce an implementation plan
2. **Build**: Read `frontend-agent.md` and/or `backend-agent.md`, implement the plan
3. **Test**: Read `qa-agent.md`, generate tests for all changes
4. **Secure**: Read `security-agent.md`, audit the changes
5. **Review**: Read `reviewer-agent.md`, final quality gate

### Parallel Agent Mode (Cursor 2.0)

When running parallel agents via worktrees, each agent should:
1. Read its agent file from `.cursor/agents/`
2. Read the `.agent-id` file to know its assigned role
3. Work only within its designated file scope
4. Never modify files owned by another agent

